				\begin{document}$$s+1$$\end{document}. To detect the value change, we store the value of function X in the previous state (X_Previous) and we compare that value with the current value. When the model detects a value change, the system acts as defined by rules. An example is the requirement ELS-19: the low beam headlamps are activated if engine has been stopped. We have captured the key state mutation by checking the value of keyState_Previous compared to keyState.

